WEBVTT

00:00.237 --> 00:03.507
At a preview event for the Consumer Electronics Show in Las Vegas,...

00:03.638 --> 00:07.033
...new tech was flying, leaping and lighting up.

00:07.645 --> 00:12.831
The LG G Flex offers a glimpse of the shape of smartphones to come: curves.

00:13.009 --> 00:16.125
So it's the world's first curved, flexible smartphone.

00:16.537 --> 00:18.733
If you're holding it to your face, it contours your face,...

00:18.838 --> 00:22.224
...brings that mic a little bit closer to you, giving you a better sound experience.

00:22.485 --> 00:23.979
Also, it fits in the palm of your hand.

00:24.377 --> 00:28.101
The possibilities of what we can do with our smartphones continue to grow.

00:28.478 --> 00:33.255
This is the Jumping Sumo which can be controlled from your mobile phone or tablet.

00:33.580 --> 00:38.303
It may be a small robot but it's robust and can leap two and a half feet into the air.

00:38.633 --> 00:43.085
And like a cat that always lands on its feet, the Sumo always lands on its wheels.

00:43.399 --> 00:46.970
The mobile QWERTY turns the traditional keyboard on end.

00:47.240 --> 00:49.755
A full QWERTY keyboard that's been split and rotated...

00:49.843 --> 00:51.809
...so that I've still got it underneath both hands.

00:52.221 --> 00:54.812
TREWGrip is a handheld Bluetooth mouse and keyboard.

00:55.184 --> 00:57.891
I don't need to find a surface where I can use my keyboard.

00:58.069 --> 01:00.432
Wearable tech is a star attraction this year.

01:00.905 --> 01:05.405
Designed for athletes, the Reebok CHECKLIGHT is a sensor device that fits into a skullcap...

01:05.759 --> 01:08.434
...and detects impact and possible head injuries.

01:08.521 --> 01:09.995
It's a three-light LED system.

01:10.076 --> 01:12.125
It's a green for on and functioning,...

01:12.551 --> 01:15.137
...yellow for moderate impact and red for more severe.

01:15.479 --> 01:18.189
There are plenty of wearables that tell you how active you are.

01:18.523 --> 01:20.027
June does something different.

01:20.260 --> 01:23.895
It tracks your exposure to the sun, and depending on your skin type,...

01:24.009 --> 01:27.947
...it'll tell you when to get out of the sun and when to break out the sunscreen.

